# VERIDION API - Master Project Rules

You are working on **Veridion API**, a standalone HTTP service with its **own database** and migrations. It is **not** veridion-nexus.

## ALWAYS READ FIRST
- `PROJECT_REFERENCE.md` - the definitive project reference (v3.2, updated 2026-04-07)

## WHAT THIS PROJECT IS
- Standalone REST API (Rust/Actix-web) + Sovereign Shield dashboard (Next.js 14, port 3000) + Landing page with signup (Next.js 14, port 3001, veridion-landing/)
- Own PostgreSQL database with own migrations (001–027+)
- No shared code or migration path with veridion-nexus
- Multi-tenant SaaS: one shared instance, all tenants isolated by tenant_id

## THREE PILLARS (CORE FEATURES)
1. **Sovereign Shield** — International data transfer monitoring and enforcement (GDPR Art. 44–49)
2. **Evidence Vault** — Immutable, cryptographically sealed audit trail (hash chains, Nexus Seals)
3. **Human Oversight** — EU AI Act Art. 14 human review queue for REVIEW decisions

## FEATURE FLOW
- **Sovereign Shield** → Evaluates transfers, returns ALLOW/BLOCK/REVIEW, creates evidence
- **Review Queue** → When SS triggers REVIEW, creates review entry for human decision
- **Evidence Vault** → Stores all evidence (SS decisions + human decisions), append-only

## SIX DESIGN DECISIONS (NEVER VIOLATE)
1. Strictest-wins aggregation — Any BLOCK = final BLOCK
2. REVIEW as safe default — Insufficient context = REVIEW, not ALLOW
3. Evidence is immutable — Append-only, never UPDATE or DELETE on evidence_events
4. Hash chain integrity — Every event links to previous via `previous_hash`
5. Nexus Seal required — SHA-256(`payload_hash` + `previous_hash` + salt)
6. Human oversight for REVIEW — All REVIEW decisions go to Review Queue

## MULTI-TENANCY RULES (NEVER VIOLATE)
- Every data query MUST filter by `tenant_id` (evidence_events, scc_registries, compliance_records, human_oversight, system_settings)
- API key auth middleware runs on all /api/v1/* routes
- Exempt from auth: GET /health, GET /api/v1/auth/dev-bypass, POST /api/v1/auth/register
- Admin routes (/api/v1/admin/*) require is_admin = true; they are the ONLY routes that may query without tenant_id filter
- api_key_hash is NEVER returned in any API response
- rate_limit_per_minute is stored in tenants table but NOT enforced until Phase 1
- Dev bypass: RUST_ENV=development + missing auth header → inject admin TenantContext automatically
- Signup exempt: POST /api/v1/auth/register has no tenant auth — it creates the tenant

## LANGUAGE RULES (NEVER VIOLATE)
- Never say "compliant", "certified", "guaranteed compliance", "X% compliant"
- Always say "provides structured, time-bound evidence" or "supports demonstrable compliance"

## TECHNOLOGY
### Backend (Rust)
- Rust 2021, Actix-web 4, PostgreSQL + SQLx, JWT/bcrypt, sha2 crate (SHA-256)
- Pattern: web::Data<PgPool> — no AppState struct
- Middleware: .wrap() — tenant auth middleware wraps all /api/v1/* routes
- TenantContext injected via req.extensions_mut().insert(...), extracted via req.extensions().get::<TenantContext>()

### Dashboard (Next.js)
- Next.js 14 (App Router), React 18, Tailwind CSS 3.x, lucide-react, react-simple-maps
- Port 3000; API calls via relative URLs proxied to backend (avoids CORS)
- Theme: dark (slate-900/800/700), emerald accents, Inter + JetBrains Mono fonts

## CRITICAL TYPES
- `TenantContext` in `src/tenant.rs` — tenant_id, name, mode, plan, is_admin
- `EvidenceEventRow` in `src/models/mod.rs` — immutable audit event
- `Decision` enum: ALLOW, BLOCK, REVIEW
- `EventSeverity`: L1 (critical), L2 (high), L3 (medium), L4 (low)
- Regulatory tags: GDPR, DORA, NIS2, AI_ACT

## SOURCE FILES
### Backend (src/)
- `main.rs` — entry point, route registration, middleware setup
- `tenant.rs` — TenantContext, TenantRow, sha256_hex helper, load_admin_tenant
- `middleware_tenant.rs` — API key auth middleware
- `models/mod.rs` — all domain models
- `evidence.rs` — Evidence Vault core logic
- `shield.rs` — Sovereign Shield decision engine
- `review_queue.rs` — Human Oversight logic
- `routes_auth.rs` — POST /api/v1/auth/register (signup, rate limiting, tenant+user creation)
- `email.rs` — SMTP welcome email via lettre (async, graceful degradation)
- `routes_evidence.rs` — /api/v1/evidence/*
- `routes_shield.rs` — /api/v1/shield/*, /api/v1/scc-registries/*, /api/v1/settings
- `routes_review_queue.rs` — /api/v1/review-queue/*, /api/v1/action/*
- `routes_admin.rs` — /api/v1/admin/* (admin only, cross-tenant)
- `routes_agents.rs` — /api/v1/agents/* (agent registry, per-agent policy)

### Dashboard (dashboard/)
- `app/utils/api.ts` — API client, all fetch functions, types
- `app/page.tsx` — Sovereign Shield home
- `app/transfer-log/page.tsx` — Transfer Log
- `app/transfer-detail/[id]/page.tsx` — Transfer Detail
- `app/review-queue/page.tsx` — Review Queue
- `app/scc-registry/page.tsx` — SCC Registry
- `app/adequate-countries/page.tsx` — Adequate Countries (static)
- `app/agents/page.tsx` — Agent Registry (registered + unregistered)
- `app/evidence-vault/page.tsx` — Evidence Vault
- `app/components/Sidebar.tsx` — Nav (branding: VERIDION nexus / Compliance Dashboard v1.0.0; System: AI System Registry, ACM Overview; `/acm/oversight` and `/acm/transfers` not in sidebar)
- `app/components/SovereignMap.tsx` + `WorldMap.tsx` — transfer map
- `app/config/countries.ts` — country classifications, getLegalBasis helpers

## MIGRATIONS
- `./migrations/` only, numbered 001–027+
- Key tables: users, tenants, compliance_records, human_oversight, evidence_events, scc_registries, system_settings
- Migration 026 adds: tenants table, tenant_id to all data tables, admin tenant seed
- Migration 027 adds: FK constraint users.company_id → tenants.id
- Never reference paths outside this project

## CONFIGURATION
| Variable | Required | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| DATABASE_URL | Yes | PostgreSQL connection string |
| SERVER_HOST | No | Bind host (default 0.0.0.0) |
| SERVER_PORT | No | Bind port (default 8080) |
| ALLOWED_ORIGINS | No | CORS origins |
| RUST_ENV | No | development = dev-bypass enabled |
| JWT_SECRET | No | JWT secret |
| MIGRATIONS_PATH | No | Override migrations dir |
| RESET_MIGRATIONS | No | Re-run all migrations (one-time) |
| NEXUS_SEAL_SALT | No | Salt for Nexus Seal SHA-256 |
| SMTP_HOST | No | SMTP server (e.g. smtp.resend.com) |
| SMTP_PORT | No | SMTP port (default 587) |
| SMTP_USER | No | SMTP username |
| SMTP_PASSWORD | No | SMTP password or API key |
| SMTP_FROM | No | From address (default noreply@veridion-nexus.eu) |

